# ── Reference-creator research corpus: binary scratch ──
# Frame extracts, downloaded source reels, and curated reference clips are kept
# on disk locally (the validation HTML and analysis reference them) but are NOT
# tracked in git: ~1.1 GB of regenerable inputs would bloat history permanently.
# We DO track the written research artifacts: ANALYSIS.md, analyzed-videos.json,
# picks-*.json, animation-ranges-*.json, CREATORS.md, and per-video metadata.json.
references/**/*.jpg
references/**/*.jpeg
references/**/*.png
references/**/*.webp
references/**/*.gif
references/**/*.mp4
references/**/*.mov
references/**/*.webm
references/**/*.m4a
# Raw yt-dlp dumps + partial downloads (machine output, not hand-authored)
references/**/*.info.json
references/**/*.mp4.json
references/**/*.part
# docs/ research assets (frames + curated motion clips) — kept on disk, not in git
docs/research/**/*.mp4
docs/research/**/*.mov
docs/research/**/*.webm
docs/**/*.jpg
docs/**/*.jpeg
docs/**/*.png
docs/**/*.gif
docs/**/*.webp

# Generated TTS voiceover samples (regenerable from scripts)
public/voiceover-*.mp3

# Auto-edit staged base clips + matte PNG sequences (regenerable)
public/autoedit/
public/matte/
